[SN]TITLE[SN]
Telecoms engineer 'critical' after Wolverhampton crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 16-year-old was arrested on suspicion of dangerous driving after two telecoms engineers were hit by a car.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The engineers, in their 20s, were believed to have been working on a communications box in Wolverhampton just before midday.
One was airlifted to hospital with "critical" head injuries. The second suffered facial and arm injuries.
Police said two people in a Citroen Picasso fled the scene after the incident.
Anyone who saw the crash at the junction of Jack Holden Avenue and Robert Wynd in Woodcross was urged to contact West Midlands Police on 101.
